WILNER, et al.
v.
The CEDARS OF CHAPEL HILL, LLC, et al. No. 234P15-1. Supreme Court of North Carolina. Sept. 24, 2015. James T. Williams, Jr., Greensboro, for the Cedars of Chapel Hill, LLC, et al. Jennifer K. Van Zant, Greensboro, for the Cedars of Chapel Hill, LLC, et al. D.J. O'Brien, III, Greensboro, for the Cedars of Chapel Hill, LLC, et al. Benjamin R. Kuhn, Raleigh, for Wilner, Jonathan, et al. Amie C. Sivon, Raleigh, for Wilner, Diane, et al. R. Michael Pipkin, Chapel Hill, for Wilner, Diane, et al. Paul Stam, Apex, for N.C. Association of Realtors.

Opinion

The following order has been entered on the motion filed on the 7th of August 2015 by Defendants to Strike Motion for Leave to File Amicus Curiae Brief:

"Motion Dismissed as moot by order of the Court in conference, this the 24th of September 2015."
